# OK-series catalysts

### Application

Series of sulfonic acid catalysts for furan resins. Enable fine control over mixture pot life.

## Features and benefits

- One system for all temperature and mold sizes.
- Stable acidity and reproducible results.
- Free from phenol and formaldehyde.
- Low odor and improved working conditions.
- Compatible with all FK resins.

## Technical specifications

| Grade | Total acidity (%) | Pot life (20 °C) | Highlights                   |
| ----- | ----------------- | ---------------- | ---------------------------- |
| OK-12 | 42–45             | 1–3 min          | Fast for small cores         |
| OK-9  | 30–35             | 3–5 min          | Universal choice             |
| OK-3  | 24–28             | 5–7 min          | Balanced speed and stability |
| OK-4  | 20–24             | 7–10 min         | For large molds              |
| OK-5  | 16–20             | 10–12 min        | For hot conditions           |

## Usage

Add to sand before resin. Recommended: 20–25% of resin weight. Catalyst grade selected by shop temperature and mold size.

## Packaging and storage

Supplied in 20 kg cans, 240 kg drums. Store cool and dry, away from alkalis. Shelf life: 6 months.

